        "content": "<p>I'm trying to use <code>obtain</code>/<code>rcases</code> for a value of <code>Lex</code>, and it doesn't work properly. Is this a bug? Am I doing something wrong?<br>\nEither it doesn't do anything:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tactic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕ₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LinearOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕ₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">False</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">obtain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rcases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  α: Type u_1</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  b: Lex (α ⊕ α)</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  inst✝: LinearOrder α</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  a: Lex (α ⊕ α)</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ha: a &lt; b</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ⊢ False</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  -/</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">trace_state</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">done</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Or it eliminates, but without <code>toLex</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tactic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕ₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LinearOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕ₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">False</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">obtain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨⟨</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  α: Type u_1</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  b: Lex (α ⊕ α)</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  inst✝: LinearOrder α</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  a: α</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ha: Sum.inl a &lt; b</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ⊢ False</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"cm\">  α: Type u_1</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  b: Lex (α ⊕ α)</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  inst✝: LinearOrder α</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  a: α</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ha: Sum.inr a &lt; b</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ⊢ False</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  -/</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">trace_state</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">done</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>for comparison, here is what I'm expecting:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕ₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LinearOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕ₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">False</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">obtain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">cases'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rcases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  α: Type u_1</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  b: Lex (α ⊕ α)</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  inst✝: LinearOrder α</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  a: α</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ha: toLex (Sum.inl a) &lt; b</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ⊢ False</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"cm\">  α: Type u_1</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  b: Lex (α ⊕ α)</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  inst✝: LinearOrder α</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  a: α</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ha: toLex (Sum.inr a) &lt; b</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ⊢ False</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  -/</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">trace_state</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">done</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 459406973,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1723191839
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think this will work with <code>let</code>, as long as you write the <code>.toLex</code> explicitly</p>",
        "id": 459412447,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1723193386
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How? <code>let ⟨toLex a, ha⟩ := h</code> doesn't work</p>",
        "id": 459412622,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1723193435
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Does it work with <code>.toLex</code>?</p>",
        "id": 459412735,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1723193485
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess it's an equiv so probably not</p>",
        "id": 459412787,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1723193506
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Nope</p>",
        "id": 459412878,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1723193524
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What's the error?</p>",
        "id": 459412944,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1723193559
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">invalid</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dotted</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">identifier</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">notation</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unknown</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">identifier</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`Sum.toLex</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">expected</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">type</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">Lex</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 459413065,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1723193629
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And without the <code>.</code>?</p>",
        "id": 459413179,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1723193667
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Huh, \"too many arguments\"</p>",
        "id": 459414905,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1723194096
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Lex</code> is a type synonym, so <code>rcases</code> doesn't know that it needs to unfold it.</p>",
        "id": 459478722,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1723211300
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As a workaround, you can <code>rcases toLex.surjective a</code></p>",
        "id": 459478810,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1723211344
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We can also try to add a custom <code>cases</code> eliminator, but I don't know which tactics will take it into account with our current setup.</p>",
        "id": 459478916,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1723211377
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"214703\">Yury G. Kudryashov</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/Obtain.20misses.20.60toLex.60/near/459478916\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We can also try to add a custom <code>cases</code> eliminator, but I don't know which tactics will take it into account with our current setup.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><code>rcases</code> doesn't pay attention to <code>cases_eliminator</code></p>",
        "id": 459481147,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1723211934
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I've had many similar such issues with <code>toLex</code>.</p>\n<p>Here's <a href=\"#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/Modify.20how.20rcases.20matches/near/442114023\">something useful</a> from when I asked something similar from <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"306601\">@Kyle Miller</span> </p>\n<p>To quote it:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lex</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sumCasesOn</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">β</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">motive</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕ₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">β</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Sort</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕ₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">β</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">inlₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">motive</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Sum</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inlₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"o\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">inrₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">β</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">motive</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Sum</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inrₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">motive</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">Sum</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">casesOn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inlₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inrₗ</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⊕ₗ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">β</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">cases'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">using</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lex</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sumCasesOn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ⊢ Sum.inlₗ a = Sum.inlₗ a</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ⊢ Sum.inrₗ a = Sum.inrₗ a</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  -/</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I've had other issues with <code>Lex</code> in these other threads in case you're curious:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/match.20with.20toLex/near/446986216\">match does strange things</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/.E2.9C.94.20inl_le_inl_iff.20without.20toLex/near/440241674\">generally fighting with it</a></li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 459679740,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Paul",
        "timestamp": 1723288548
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The custom eliminator feels like overkill when you can just write</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">cases'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">obtain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which is also shorter</p>",
        "id": 459680890,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1723289227
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The rule is just \"<code>obtain</code>/<code>rcases</code>/<code>match</code> make a mess in places that <code>induction</code> and <code>cases</code> do not\"</p>",
        "id": 459680977,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1723289294
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>One more point in favour of a hypothetical unified tactic <span aria-label=\"innocent\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f607\" role=\"img\" title=\"innocent\">:innocent:</span></p>",
        "id": 459698476,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1723297259
    }
